<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1896-05-08T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1896-05-08T00:00:00-05:00" n="657" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d657">
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Williams</persName> to Mr.
                                    <persName type="to">Olney</persName>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Habana</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1896-05-08"><hi rend="italic">May 8,
                                1896</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p>In case of <hi rend="italic">Competitor</hi>, trial terminated.
                            Prosecuting officer asks penalty death for all, giving precedence to the
                            local law relating to foreigners over the treaty and the protocol in
                            this case. As the court and authorities here agree on this point, I
                            inform you for such diplomatic action you may deem proper. I am
                            preparing remonstrance Captain-General as the superior delegate of Spain
                            in this island.</p>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>